This paper deals with the analysis of medical images using deep networks and probabilistic trackers, which are commonly used in computer vision (CV) and artificial intelligence (AI) applications. The use of deep networks suggests that the paper may belong to the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) sub-category. The probabilistic tracker is based on Bayesian inference, which is a common technique in machine learning and AI, suggesting that the paper may also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of particle filters, which are commonly used in machine learning and robotics, suggesting that the paper may belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG), Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE), or Robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories.
